This paper deals with security and privacy issues in computer systems, specifically in the context of Intel SGX and cryptographic routines. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a software-only defense that involves modifying the program's memory access behavior, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The defense is implemented using a compiler, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses hardware-assisted defenses, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems (cs.SY).
